Create a Nested Segment

Reuse filters and maintain consistency in your data by using an existing segment to build a new nested segment. A nested segment is a combination of an outer segment and inner segment. Each nested segment can have up to 50 filters in each tab.

Available with add-on license: Segmentation and Activation
In the segment canvas, click the Segments tab.
The list shows the segments that you can nest. You can’t nest certain segments, such as rapid segments or segments in error or inactive state, so they aren’t listed. Additionally, you can't nest a segment within a rapid segment.
Click the segment that you want to reuse. You can view the description next to the segment name.
You can’t use an outer nested segment as an inner segment, and the inner and outer segments must be in the same Segment On entity. If you edit the rules of an inner nested segment, the changes are applied to all the outer segments attached to it.
Click Edit Rules.
Drag your segment to the canvas.
You can open the segment in a different tab to review its content by clicking the arrow icon next to the segment’s name.
On the Include or Exclude tab, select the publish behavior.
To use the segment population from the most recent publish, select Use Last Published Membership. Before selecting this option, ensure that the segment has been published at least one time. With this option, the population doesn’t refresh with the outer segment publish schedule. You can use membership data from the inner segment that runs into the outer segment.
To copy segment filter criteria and refresh the segment when the outer segment publishes, select Use Segment Criteria.
Click Done, and then click Save.
